name: FeaturestoreMonitoringConfig
description:
Configuration of how features in Featurestore are monitored.

Generated from protobuf message google.cloud.aiplatform.v1.FeaturestoreMonitoringConfig

Extends Google\Protobuf\Internal\Message

params.name: data
params.description: Optional. Data for populating the Message object.

params.name: data.snapshot_analysis
params.description: The config for Snapshot Analysis Based Feature Monitoring.

params.name: data.import_features_analysis
params.description: The config for ImportFeatures Analysis Based Feature Monitoring.

params.name: data.numerical_threshold_config
params.description: Threshold for numerical features of anomaly detection. This is shared by all objectives of Featurestore Monitoring for numerical features (i.e. Features with type ([Feature.ValueType][google.cloud.aiplatform.v1.Feature.ValueType]) DOUBLE or INT64).

params.name: data.categorical_threshold_config
params.description: Threshold for categorical features of anomaly detection. This is shared by all types of Featurestore Monitoring for categorical features (i.e. Features with type ([Feature.ValueType][google.cloud.aiplatform.v1.Feature.ValueType]) BOOL or STRING).
